featured_reviews.review_id: This masjid is at mahape road. Near from ghansoli and koparkhairane station. But from both station it is 2Kmt far. You have to take rikshaw for it. Not noticable from outside. You can not easily find this masjid. The main indication is it is near to petrol pump and there is truck cleaning service is there. There will be a truck tyre and puncture repeirer. But if you ask him masjid he will not tell you adress. He will tell, there is no masjid. That masjid is very small..and constructed on hired land. There is very low space for namaz. Even a person can not go in sajda properly. Friday prayer time is 1.20 for first jamat. And due to crowed they conduct second jamat at 1.45. even if crowed is there they conduct third jamat too. I recomand you to go ghansoli dargh for juma prayer. There you will get place easily. This masjid is deobandi sunni maslak masjid. The land is not owned so. After namaz kindly contribute chanda for masjid so that land can be purchased for masjid.

featured_reviews.review_id: Agricultural Produce Market Committee (APMC) is a statutory market committee constituted by a State Government in respect of trade in certain notified agricultural/horticultural/livestock products. Mumbai Agricultural Produce Market Committee has been established on 15th January, 1977 under the provisions of the Maharashtra Agricultural Produce Marketing (Regulation and development) Act, 1963. It is a Body Corporate under Section 12 of the said Act. Amongst others, main objectives of establishment of Mumbai APMC are - to develop modern market yards for agricultural commodities, regulation of marketing of agricultural commodities, help the farmers to fetch better price for their produce, create infrastructural facilities for orderly development of trade, to maintain and manage the markets and stipulate conditions for use of markets within the market area. The Committee has been established with objectives of regulation of marketing of agricultural and certain other produce therein, establishment of markets therefore and for such incidental purposes. The Committee is required to regulate and supervise the marketing of agricultural produce in accordance with the provisions of the said Act, Rules made there under and Byelaws of the Market Committee. It is empowered to regulate entry of persons and vehicles as well as to take all possible steps to prevent adulteration and to promote and organize grading and standardization. The Committee is required to collect, maintain and supply information in respect of productions as well as storage, processing, prices and movement of the notified agricultural produce.

featured_reviews.review_id:
In Kharghar the existence of this Sunni Mosque is a great mercy of the Allah- The Merciful.

Whether locals or outsiders whoever comes here to pray , definitely its peaceful atmosphere gives a great feeling of happiness.

It's greeneries and plenty of space with trees out side the mosque let not anyone feel hassles in its shades.

It has also a Muslim cemetery ( burial ground ) which covers around 70% of its space. Rest of the 30% space is for the masjid.

The Masjid Management committee has been doing a great job. They have provided air conditioners in the main hall of the mosque .

Facility for Wudhu (ablution) & Toilet is satisfactory.

There is a plenty of space for parking available on the roadside.

Three Congregational prayer for Jumah take place here due to the huge crowd on Fridays.

The timing for the 1st Juma prayer is 1:15 Pm for 2nd 1:45 pm and for 3rd and last is 02:15pm. ( kindly cross check with the mosque management for accuracy).

On Fridays you can also find street food stalls outside the mosque, your favourite chicken biryani, Pulav, Khichda, Cutlets, Mango Milk Shakes ( in summer to quench your thirst) etc. are there.

If want to do some charity, there are many needy ones available. So keep some money while leaving to the mosque for donations.

There is a Christian cemetery and a Crematorium situated side by side as well.

Actually CIDCO has allotted lands to facilitate funeral related activities for the Muslims, Christian and Hindu Communities.

Plz like this review and ask if something left to mention or you want to know more about this place.

Wassalam !!!

Addition : Juma Prayer Schedule , Fajr , Isha & Taraweeh Schedule for Ramadan 2019 ( in picture )

The timing for the 1st Juma prayer is 1:15 Pm for 2nd 1:45 pm and for 3rd and last is 02:15pm. ( kindly cross check with the mosque management for accuracy).

On Fridays you can also find street food stalls outside the mosque, your favourite chicken biryani, Pulav, Khichda, Cutlets, Mango Milk Shakes ( in summer to quench your thirst) etc. are there.

If want to do some charity, there are many needy ones available. So keep some money while leaving to the mosque for donations.

There is a Christian cemetery and a Crematorium situated side by side as well.

Actually CIDCO has allotted lands to facilitate funeral related activities for the Muslims, Christian and Hindu Communities.

Plz like this review and ask if something left to mention or you want to know more about this place.

Wassalam !!!

2019: I reached Khargar railway station, and had to pick up an auto.

I named a nearby landmark (a hospital), but no auto-driver was willing to go with Share   (Rs 10) to the location.
In the end, hired a personal auto (Rs 40 approx) and reached the landmark. While getting off the ride, I asked the driver what to do next time to avail Share ride from the station, and he said that I should get off at NAURANG.

While in the ride, I observed the city; definitely well-developed. Felt as if I'm in the West or something. Although, in such well-off places, people seem to lose their senses regarding how to dress well. llh lmst`n

The Masjid is quite small, but well made. Alhumdulillah.

May the bless the Imam - - very nice to meet him lHmd llh.

While going back, I couldn't find auto from the surrounding area. Had to go Naurang and hire one on fare.

That's all. Almost.
The Masjid is temporary on rent, because the real masjid is under construction, and it needs funds. So please help the cause as well!

Edit 2021: The Masjid has been shifted to the new building, wllh lHmd!

The is the best location to perform Juma & 5 times daily prayer  in congregation.

The only mosque  in Takka. Although there is a famous Dargah of Hazrat Jamal Shah Baba situated alongside the Kalundre rive around 1 KM of the distance of Sunni Takka Masjid and the Panvel railway station .

A masjid is also situated in the vicinity of Dargah with plenty of space where one can Perform daily five times prayer and the weekly Juma prayer as well.

The Sunni Takka masjid can accommodate around 500 people at a time.

A Maktab is also run by the masjid committee for the kids.

featured_reviews.review_id:
The mosque is situated in a triangle of the roads along with commercial buildings on Old Mumbai-Pune & Mumbai-Goa Roads at Palaspe Phata.

As in absence of foot over bridge it's always challenging to get to the mosque especially for older people and the kids.

I don't know if the government has a plan to make the one at this place or not.

On Fridays there is always a huge crowd gathering to offer the prayers.

Although the Masjid committee has done a lot to facilitate all the necessities but still the design of the mosque and the accessibilities are lacking.

It's usually we see in crowded and less developed places.

The reason for that is the ignorance of the Muslims towards the masjid fundings.

They spent a very less on this, even their monthly cigarettes  Tambakhu and Pan budgets are more than four times higher than their contributions to the mosques .

In this locality this is the only Sunni mosque needs a great attention of the local Muslims.
